    "ailments_description": "The most common ailments you can heal with Cornopteris parvisora are fever, skin infections, and rheumatism. Cornopteris parvisora contains flavonoids and phenolic acids that exhibit antimicrobial properties, effectively treating skin infections by inhibiting the growth of pathogens. Additionally, its anti-inflammatory properties help alleviate joint pain associated with rheumatism, allowing individuals to regain mobility and function. By reducing inflammation and promoting wound healing, Cornopteris parvisora also aids in the treatment of fever by mitigating its symptoms and supporting the body's natural recovery process. Furthermore, its antioxidant properties protect the body from oxidative stress, which can exacerbate various health conditions, including those mentioned above.",
