    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Cornopteris parvisora are flavonoids, terpenoids, and phenolic acids, which have been found to possess antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and antimicrobial properties. Flavonoids, specifically quercetin and kaempferol, have been identified as key contributors to the plant's bioactive profile, exhibiting potential anti-cancer and cardiovascular benefits. Terpenoids, such as borneol and bornyl acetate, have been shown to possess analgesic and anti-inflammatory effects, while phenolic acids like ferulic acid have been found to possess antioxidant properties, protecting against oxidative stress and cell damage. The combination of these compounds in Cornopteris parvisora may contribute to the plant's traditional uses in treating various health conditions, including fever, rheumatism, and skin infections. Further research is needed to fully elucidate the mechanisms of action and potential therapeutic applications of these constituents.",
