    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Cornopteris parvisora are infusion, tea, tincture, decoction, and salve. Infusion and decoction are aqueous preparations made by steeping the dried leaves or aerial parts in hot water to create a liquid extract for medicinal use. Tincture is a concentrated liquid extract made by soaking the plant material in a solvent such as ethanol, often used for internal consumption. Tea is a less concentrated infusion prepared for oral consumption, typically with hot water, while salve is a topical preparation made from the plant's oil or fat-soluble extracts, used to treat skin conditions. These preparations are made from Cornopteris parvisora due to its reported medicinal properties, including antioxidant and anti-inflammatory activities.",
